snippet.textDisplay: It should be noted that Soz o Salam is not something to 'sing', instead it is 'recited'. Also, it is never recited with music and the absence of music does not undermine its effectiveness. Alternatively, it must not be called "Soz o Salam". Soazkhwani is not something new in India. We appreciate the spirit of participants in this recital but they are supposed to know the norms of Soazkhwani.
snippet.textOriginal: It should be noted that Soz o Salam is not something to 'sing', instead it is 'recited'. Also, it is never recited with music and the absence of music does not undermine its effectiveness. Alternatively, it must not be called "Soz o Salam". Soazkhwani is not something new in India. We appreciate the spirit of participants in this recital but they are supposed to know the norms of Soazkhwani.

It Says: "Us ku Muzah , Gham-e-Shah (A.S) jis Nay gawarah na kiyah. Yani Abbas (A.S) Nay Jee Bhai Say Pyara Na kiyah"
Actually it is a tribute to Hazrat Abbas (A.S), who was the step-bother of Hazrat Imam Hussain (A.S). 
In english it can be translated as, "Our message of repect & greetings to Hazrat Abbas (A.S) who didnt bear the sorrow of Imam Hussain (A.S) and he gave no worth to his life and stand with his brother till martyrdom"
Actually this is referring to the incident of  Karabala.
